{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ce22dae1-6762-4b24-8bc6-8b5964e7029e","content":"**Yes, there will be a compatibility issue.**\n\nMSTest v3 requires **.NET 6.0 or later** — it dropped support for .NET 5.0 (which itself has been out of support since May 2022).\n\nTo upgrade to MSTest v3 you have two options:\n\n1. **Upgrade your target framework first** — change `net5.0` to `net6.0` (or ideally `net8.0` LTS), then upgrade MSTest.\n2. **Stay on MSTest v2** if you must remain on .NET 5.0 (not recommended since both are EOL).\n\nThe recommended path is to update `TargetFramework` to a supported .NET version, then upgrade the MSTest packages. Want me to do that?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4ae485a7-6b13-47a1-9f7d-86f1ab27bbc1","outputTokens":178},"id":"400746b8-a505-4b51-b8c4-c8f961338e7c","timestamp":"2026-04-05T01:04:08.650Z","parentId":"57209b1b-8e68-49c5-9dbd-145a2e2797ce"}
